### Test My Subscription API
### First get a valid JWT token by calling the auth endpoint

### 1. Send OTP (to get a valid mobile number in system)
POST http://192.168.1.1:5002/api/users/auth/send-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "countryCode": "+91",
  "mobileNumber": "9876543210"
}

### 2. Verify OTP and get JWT token
POST http://192.168.1.1:5002/api/users/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "countryCode": "+91",
  "mobileNumber": "9876543210",
  "otp": "1234"
}

### 3. Test My Subscription endpoint with the token from step 2
### Replace "YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE" with the actual token from step 2
GET http://192.168.1.48:56925/api/user/subscriptions/my-subscription
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

### 4. Test without token (should return 401)
GET http://192.168.1.48:56925/api/user/subscriptions/my-subscription
Content-Type: application/json

### 5. Test with invalid token (should return 401)
GET http://192.168.1.48:56925/api/user/subscriptions/my-subscription
Authorization: Bearer invalid.token.here
Content-Type: application/json
